ration intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: com.mchange:mchange-commons-java:0.4.0\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe remaining post-generation failure was **not metadata-related**.\\n\\nThe Codex `metadata-fix` log shows it finished by noting that the metadata file validated cleanly and that the remaining native failure was an unrelated AWT/Swing crash. The Gradle/native output confirms that the crash happened when the generated Swing test initialized the event-dispatch path:\\n\\n- failing test: `tests/src/com.mchange/mchange-commons-java/0.4.0/src/test/java/com_mchange/mchange_commons_java/PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest.java`\\n- failing call path: `SwingUtilities.isEventDispatchThread()` -> `java.awt.Toolkit` initialization\\n- fatal native error: `java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: java/awt/GraphicsEnvironment`\\n- native runtime note: `Fatal error reported via JNI: FindClass java/awt/GraphicsEnvironment failed`\\n\\nThis is a native-image/AWT limitation in the generated Swing test path, not a missing reachability-metadata entry. There was no `Missing*RegistrationError` and no suggested metadata snippet to add.\\n\\n## Intervention\\n\\nRemoved the unsupported generated test:\\n\\n- deleted `tests/src/com.mchange/mchange-commons-java/0.4.0/src/test/java/com_mchange/mchange_commons_java/PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest.java`\\n\\nNo metadata files were modified.\\n\\n## Why this failure is not metadata-related\\n\\n`PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest` exercises Swing UI behavior through `PropertyBoundComboBox` and the AWT event-dispatch thread. In the native test run, that code forces `java.desktop` toolkit initialization and crashes before any library-specific missing-registration error appears.\\n\\nBecause the failure is caused by the native runtime trying to load `java/awt/GraphicsEnvironment`, removing the test is the correct intervention. Adding or changing reachability metadata for `com.mchange:mchange-commons-java` would not addre