cs/add_new_library_support.json:8188:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8222:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 74.61\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8242:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8276:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 66.93\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8296:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8310:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 100.0\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8331:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8336:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8341:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8369:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.codehaus.woodstox:stax2-api:4.2.2\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nBoth failing native tests had the same root cause: this was a metadata-related failure, not a bad test and not a native-image platform limitation. `XMLValidationSchemaFactory.newInstance(...)` looks up a custom service definition resource at `META-INF/services/org.codehaus.stax2.validation.XMLValidationSchemaFactory.dtd`. In the failing native image, that resource was not registered, so runtime lookup returned no provider and both tests failed with `FactoryConfigurationError`.\\n\\n## Failure breakdown\\n\\n### `loadsFactoryFromSystemResourcesWhenNoClassLoaderIsProvided()`\\n- **Root cause:** missing native-image resource metadata for `META-INF/services/org.codehaus.stax2.validation.XMLValidationSchemaFactory.dtd`\\n- **Why it failed:** the null-classloader path falls back to system resource lookup, but the service file was not embedded in the native image, so no `XMLValidationSchemaFactory` implementation could be found.\\n\\n### `loadsFactoryFromExplicitClassLoaderResources()`\\n- **Root cause:** same missing native-image resource metadata\\n- **Why it failed:** even with the explicit test class loader, the same service file was absent from the native image, so provider discovery failed in the same way.\\n\\n## Codex log findings\\n\\nThe Codex log shows this was already identified correctly as a metadata gap. Codex added a resource entry for:\\n\\n- `META-INF/services/org.codehaus.stax2.validation.XMLValidationSchemaFactory.dtd`\\n\\nwith condition:\\n\\n- `org.codehaus.stax2.validation.XMLValidationSchemaFactory`\\n\\nAfter that change, Codex reran `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.codehaus.woodstox:stax2-api:4.2.2 --stacktrace` and both native tests passed.\\n\\n## Remaining missing metadata\\n\\nNone. The log indicates the metadata issue was resolved by registering the service resource. There is no evidence of a remaining reflection or JNI gap behind this failure.\\n\\n## Intervention decision\\n\\n- **Did not remove any generated tests.**\\n- **Did not modify metadata files in this intervention.**\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe generated support is still valuable because it covers a real native-image compatibility requirement in `stax2-api`: runtime discovery of `XMLValidationSchemaFactory` implementations through a custom `META-INF/services/...dtd` resource. The generated test and its service file validate both lookup variants exercised by the API:\\n\\n- system-resource lookup when no class loader is provided\\n- explicit class-loader resource lookup\\n\\nRemoving that generated support would discard legitimate coverage for a real metadata requirement that Codex already fixed.\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8380:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 0.93\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8401:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8406:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8411:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8445:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 0.93\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8466:            \"coverageRatio\": 0.735294,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8471:            \"coverageRatio\": 0.5,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8476:        \"coverageRatio\": 0.710526,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8504:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.conscrypt:conscrypt-openjdk-uber:2.0.0\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nCodex fixed real metadata gaps for Conscrypt, but the remaining failures in the Gradle output were all non-metadata native-image/runtime issues. I removed the generated tests that exercised those unsupported paths and kept the generated metadata and the passing tests intact.\\n\\n## What failed\\n\\nThe Codex log shows that the metadata changes already fixed two legitimate metadata-driven failures (`OpenSSLECPrivateKeyTest` and `OpenSSLECPublicKeyTest`). The remaining five failures were:\\n\\n1. `DuckTypedPSKKeyManagerTest.invokesSocketDuckTypedPskMethodsDuringHandshake()`\\n2. `NativeLibraryLoader2Test.definesHelperClassIntoTargetClassLoaderWhenHelperCannotBeLoaded()`\\n3. `NativeLibraryLoaderTest.loadsFromOsxJnilibFallbackResourceWhenPrimaryResourceIsMissing()`\\n4. `NativeLibraryLoaderTest.loadsFromOsxDynlibFallbackResourceWhenMappedLibraryNameEndsWithJniLib()`\\n5. `OpenSSLCipherEVP_AEADTest.throwsAeadBadTagExceptionWhenDecryptingTamperedGcmCiphertext()`\\n\\n## Root cause by failure\\n\\n### 1. `DuckTypedPSKKeyManagerTest.invokesSocketDuckTypedPskMethodsDuringHandshake()`\\n\\nThis failed with `java.net.SocketException: Socket is closed` from `org.conscrypt.NativeSsl.doHandshake(...)` during the live socket handshake path.\\n\\nWhy this is not metadata-related:\\n- there is no `Missing*RegistrationError`\\n- the failure happens inside the socket/file-descriptor handshake path after startup, not during reflection/resource lookup\\n- the engine-based PSK test in the same class passes, so the generated support still covers the PSK duck-typing behavior that is actually working in native-image\\n\\nAction taken:\\n- removed only the socket-based PSK test method from `DuckTypedPSKKeyManagerTest.java`\\n\\n### 2. `NativeLibraryLoader2Test.definesHelperClassIntoTargetClassLoaderWhenHelperCannotBeLoaded()`\\n\\nThis failed with `UnsupportedFeatureError: Classes cannot be defined at runtime by default when using ahead-of-time Native Image compilation` while Conscrypt tried to define `org.conscrypt.NativeLibraryUtil` into another class loader.\\n\\nWhy this is not metadata-related:\\n- runtime class definition is a native-image capability limitation, not a reachability metadata gap\\n- the error explicitly points to runtime class loading / predefined classes support, not reflection/resource metadata\\n\\nAction taken:\\n- removed `NativeLibraryLoader2Test.java`\\n\\n### 3. `NativeLibraryLoaderTest.loadsFromOsxJnilibFallbackResourceWhenPrimaryResourceIsMissing()`\\n### 4. `NativeLibraryLoaderTest.loadsFromOsxDynlibFallbackResourceWhenMappedLibraryNameEndsWithJniLib()`\\n\\nBoth tests failed with `expected: 1 but was: 0` because the macOS fallback resource lookup path was never entered in the native executable.\\n\\nWhy this is not metadata-related:\\n- the assertions fail because the code path was not taken at all, not because a resource was missing from metadata\\n- these tests simulate macOS behavior by mutating `os.name`, but native-image preserves the host platform behavior from image build/runtime initialization, so the Linux-built native test binary does not exercise the macOS fallback branch as expected\\n- the remaining `NativeLibraryLoaderTest` still validates the helper-class resource path that does work in native-image\\n\\nAction taken:\\n- removed the two macOS fallback test methods\\n- simplified `NativeLibraryLoaderTest.java` to keep only the passing helper-class coverage\\n\\n### 5. `OpenSSLCipherEVP_AEADTest.throwsAeadBadTagExceptionWhenDecryptingTamperedGcmCiphertext()`\\n\\nThis failed with `SecurityException: Attempted to verify a provider that was not registered at build time: org.conscrypt.OpenSSLProvider`.\\n\\nWhy this is not metadata-related:\\n- this is a native-image security-provider registration/verification issue, not a missing reachability entry in `reachability-metadata.json`\\n- the failure comes from JCE provider verification rules during native execution, not from missing reflection/resource serialization metadata\\n\\nAction taken:\\n- removed `OpenSSLCipherEVP_AEADTest.java`\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should still be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support is still valuable and should stay because Codex did fix real metadata problems:\\n- the Codex log reports that the generated metadata resolved the failures in `OpenSSLECPrivateKeyTest` and `OpenSSLECPublicKeyTest`\\n- after removing only the non-metadata tests above, the library-scoped run succeeds with the rest of the generated support still in place\\n- the surviving test suite continues to validate meaningful Conscrypt behavior in native-image, including TLS engine handshakes, provider integration, platform/socket wrapping, trust-manager reflective access, native library loading helper behavior, and EC key serialization/deserialization\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\nVerified with:\\n\\n```bash\\n./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.conscrypt:conscrypt-openjdk-uber:2.0.0 --stacktrace\\n```\\n\\nResult: build successful, `13` native tests passed, `0` failed.\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8515:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 25.59\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8535:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8569:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 43.77\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/metadata-forge-metrics/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8590:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/